issue.body:
Duplicate elements are rolled up into one. This has been confirmed for `<td>` and `<span>`. Below is sample HTML and the result that is printed to console.

Tested on jsoup v1.8.2.

``` java
System.out.println(Jsoup.parse("<html><body><table><tr><td> VALUE </td><td> VALUE </td></tr></table></body></html>").select("td:nth-child(1)"));
// <td> VALUE </td>
// <td> VALUE </td>

System.out.println(Jsoup.parse("<html><body><table><tr><td> VALUE </td><td> VALUE </td></tr></table></body></html>").select("td:nth-child(2)"));
// (Prints newline only)

System.out.println(Jsoup.parse("<html><body><table><tr><td> VALUE </td><td> VALUE2 </td></tr></table></body></html>").select("td:nth-child(1)"));
// <td> VALUE </td>

System.out.println(Jsoup.parse("<html><body><table><tr><td> VALUE </td><td> VALUE2 </td></tr></table></body></html>").select("td:nth-child(2)"));
// <td> VALUE2 </td>

System.out.println(Jsoup.parse("<html><body><table><tr><td> VALUE </td><td> VALUE </td></tr></table></body></html>").select("td:last-child"));
// (Prints newline only)
```

